The December contribution of 600 crowns to pensioners is at risk.
&quot;It is the justice of equal stomachs, it has nothing to do with human justice,&quot; said TOP 09 vice-chairman Miroslav Kalousek, who emphasized the principle of merit.
The chairman of the ODS deputies, Zbyněk Stanjura, noted that the one-time contribution sounds good, but in the long term it would be better if it were in a standard valuation, because it would be reflected in the following years.
&quot;We have room to find a mechanism to arrange this,&quot; Stanjura said.
He supported the original proposal of Minister Michaela Marksová (ČSSD), according to which it was to be valorized beyond the scope of the law next year.
Marks defended the subsidy with the argument that it will improve the social situation of pensioners, which according to her is not rosy.
