FedEx earnings mixed, cut fiscal 2016 outlook
FedEx reported disappointing results for the latest quarter and a huge cut in its full-year profit forecast due to weak freight demand and higher costs for its ground division.
The company also said it plans to hire about 55,000 seasonal workers over the holidays.
This time last year, FedEx announced it would hire 50,000 seasonal workers for the holidays.
The company&#39;s shares fell about 2.5 percent in premarket trading 45 minutes before the open on Wednesday.
FedEx says it expects earnings between $10.40 and $10.90 for the fiscal year ending next May, down 20 cents from its previous forecast.
