The lowered outlook comes despite a 4.9 percent increase in interest rates on average, which will take effect in January. 4, and higher surcharges for ground transport of heavy or large parcels starting in November.
The company said it still expects profit to grow from a year ago due to cost-cutting, higher revenue and growth in online trading.
