But a boom in online shopping has boosted results at FedEx&#39;s ground unit.
Ground revenue rose 29 percent in the latest quarter, but operating profit was essentially flat due to higher prices for larger packages and self-insurance.
The express unit saw higher income due to higher base rates, while profit declined in the freight business due to higher labor costs.
FedEx shares fell $3.85, or 2.5 percent, to $150.15 in premarket trading about an hour before the open.
